There is a particular silence after a film truly works—the few seconds before anyone reaches for a phone or remembers the practical world outside the screen.

## The feeling after

This was less about a clever plot than the accumulation of small glances, missed timing, and things left unsaid. The final scene did not explain everything. It trusted the quiet.

I watched it at the cineplex, and the walk home felt like an unofficial final act.
